The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | At Rs 300 crore a piece, flying office for VVIPs
                                                                                                                                                 1                                                                                Chopper for VVIPs
        SUJAN DUTTA                      A 12 Agusta Westland-101 helicopter                                
	New Delhi, Jan. 24: Bigger offices in the sky and more comfortable travel await the Prime Minister, President and VVIPs for whom the Indian Air Force is likely to contract 12 helicopters shortly.        
	The IAFs Headquarters Communication Squadron  as the VVIP squadron is known  will add 12 Agusta Westland-101 helicopters estimated to cost upwards of Rs 300 crore each.        
	The IAF has chosen the AW-101 over Sikorskys S-92 Superhawk after evaluating them in trials. The trials were conducted by both the Indian Air Force and the Special Protection Group (SPG), the wing of the National Security Guard assigned to VVIP duties.        
	The Cabinet committee on security is understood to have approved the purchase. Over the past three years, the number of VVIP aircraft in the Headquarters Squadron has grown steadily.        
	The AW101 combines the most advanced technologies, mission systems and manufacturing expertise with a proven aircraft design. With the largest cabin in its class and with stand-up head room, excellent safety features and incorporating the latest in vibration reduction technology the AW101 is ideally suited to both the VVIP head of state transport and to long range roles such as search and rescue and disaster relief operated by government agencies, says Agusta Westland about the helicopter.        
	The AW-101 will join a fleet of other new aircraft  five Embraer 135 Legacy jets and three Boeing Business Jets  in the VVIP squadron. The VVIP aircraft are equipped with self-protection suites, chaff dispensers and the latest communication instruments.                                                                                                                                          
